<dita xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/"><concept id="FAR_6_204" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc=""><title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">6.204</ph> Section 8(a) competition.</title><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><ol id="d371e13" class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d385e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
						             To fulfill statutory requirements relating to section 8(a) of the Small Business Act, as amended by Public Law 100-656, contracting officers may limit competition to eligible 8(a) participants (see <xref href="Subpart_19.8.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_8" base="i1099848" outputclass="fm:Subpart" class="- topic/xref ">subpart  19.8</xref>).</p>
            </li><li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d385e18"> <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> No separate justification or determination and findings is required under this part to limit competition to eligible 8(a) participants. (But see <xref href="6.302-5.dita#FAR_6_302_5" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly" class="- topic/xref ">6.302-5</xref> and <xref href="6.303-1.dita#FAR_6_303_1" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly" class="- topic/xref ">6.303-1</xref> for sole source 8(a) awards over <ph rev="FAC 2025-06 October 1, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2024-001?>$30 million<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 6.204 in paragraph (b) by removing “$25 million” and adding “$30 million” in its place.?></ph>.) </p>
            </li></ol></conbody></concept></dita>